Today's episode of What’s The Juice is LIVE for pod Monday 🎉 and it's called "YUP THAT'S A SIGN" - the 'out there' episode where @thelovelyalea and I don't hold back about mediumship, her gifts, our unexplainable dreams and experiences, the magic of life, signs, spirituality, and most of all... the deeper meaning of 2020.⁣
⁣
This year has been a tough one, but also a life-changing one where "2020 vision" has given us the ability to see what we no longer want for our lives and our world, and how we can to move forward and rebuild with a new plan and path in mind. ⁣
⁣
While this episode is a lot more spiritual than our usual topics, I think it's just what we all need to finish out the year strong and reflect on our own gifts and sense of purpose that have been revealed throughout this wild ride. In today's IGTV, @thelovelyalea will not only be giving me a mini-reading so that you can get a feel for what she does... she's also doing a full on reading for all of YOU, the collective of incredible humans who were meant to be alive during such a transformative time on earth. If you’ve been feeling hopeless or stressed about the “thorns” of this year, I think Alea’s reading will remind you of the “rose” on the other side of the pain.⁣
⁣
SPEAKING OF WHICH, WE’RE DOING ANOTHER IMPROMPTU GIVEAWAY 😇 ⁣
⁣
Leave a comment on this post with your very own “rose” and “thorn” of 2020 (thorn being a pain point that caused you to have to reexamine or rework your life, and rose being the most important lesson or gem you got from this year — perhaps it was even a lesson you got from that thorn). I want to hear YOUR experience of what 2020 has meant for you and shown you, and how you’re finding meaning too 💜⁣
⁣
I’ll pick two winners to receive a formula of their choice, and one winner to receive a free 30 minute reading with @thelovelyalea ✨

In Traditional Chinese Medicine (TCM), your stomach digests food thanks to something called “stomach fire” or “digestive fire.” ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Think of this as a roaring internal fire that you want to ignite first thing in the morning to get you up and going, by nourishing your stomach with heat from tea & warm, nourishing foods. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
You want keep adding consistent “logs” of food throughout the day to keep it from burning out (not skipping meals or eating in a rush helps)… and the LAST thing you want to do, is pour ice cold water over that fire. As Amrit says, this “fire” is very much akin to the Western concept of hydrochloric acid, which is essential not only for digestion, but absorption too.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⚡️“If you consume cold food or liquids, it’s putting out this fire. Now foods are sticking around longer, you won’t absorb as much, you’re going to be hungrier, you’re going to get bloated. Foods that are closer to your internal body temperature are just so much easier for your body to digest.” - @6babebeauty⁣⁣
⁣⁣
⚡️”To cool down in the summer, it’s better to consume foods that have a cooling nature like watermelon or mint tea versus frozen, chilled, or iced drinks. Cold beverages are neither healthy nor cooling; in fact, they cause the stomach to create more heat in order to break the foods down, which ultimately damages the entire digestive system.” - Gail Reichstein⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Chinese Medicine takes this a step further, as preserving the warmth of the stomach supplies the Kidney meridian with the warmth needed to function optimally, especially when it comes to hormone health and fertility.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
“There’s a Ming Men fire between your Kidneys. That’s also always burning, and that’s our deeper reserve of energy. For my fertility patients, this is very important. You’re now an incubator, everything has to be warm and covered, like you’re covering an incubator! Imagine you were hatching little ducklings, you would never put a fan there.”⁣⁣
⁣⁣
In TCM, “Kidneys” and the Kidney meridian encompass far more than the physical organs in Western physiology and includes our reproductive and endocrine health. CONTINUED 👇🏼👇🏼

This week’s podcast episode of #WhatsTheJuice is on my favorite topic: SKIN HEALTH, TIPS & TRICKS 😍! If you have just ~10 minutes to give your face a little love, Amrit Singh of @6babebeauty is about to walk us through 3 insanely quick and easy face massage techniques you can do right now at home.⁣
⁣
⭐️We start off with technique #1: using a simple roller to cool, de-puff, and fight inflammation around the eyes. She shows us how ‘gentle’ can still be wildly effective, as we’re using the stone’s inherently cold temperature to soothe irritation and puffiness (as we also lightly pulse it downwards to move fluid retention).⁣
⁣
⭐️Then technique #2: involves using a Gua Sha tool and her “eraser technique” to smooth and work on the “11 lines” between the brows which can happen when we’re squinting at a computer all day! This technique brings fresh blood flow to the area and encourages your own collagen production.⁣
⁣
⭐️Lastly, technique #3: uses only your own two hands as we do the coolest lip plumping massage that releases ALL of that emotional tension we hold around the mouth when we’re stressed and clenching! The muscle tension we release here is what’s responsible for “laugh lines,” so she’s giving us allll the tricks for aging gracefully, naturally✨⁣
⁣
If you loved this, do not miss this “THE SKIN EPISODE” (#26) where Amrit spills the juice on:⁣
🔻 COSMETIC ACUPUNCTURE as an alternative to botox and filler⁣
🔻 do collagen supplements actually = collagen in skin?⁣
🔻 how she cleared her acne (and why HOT BATHS were key)⁣
🔻 why she doesn’t wear crop tops (and always has socks/an undershirt on)⁣
🔻 how to protect your immune system during this summer->fall cold weather transition⁣
🔻 what ACTUALLY makes us glow (hint: not topical serums)⁣
🔻 how to protect your YIN (our hydration, plumpness + lubrication!)⁣
⁣
🎧 Search “What’s The Juice” wherever podcasts are available to listen 😘

NEW 👏🏼 EPISODE 👏🏼 IS 👏🏼 LIVE 👏🏼 ⁣
⁣
...and one of the most IMPORTANT to date! ⁣
⁣
Your lymphatic system is *the* largest circulatory system in your body – yes, twice as big as your circulatory system! 🩸 Yet, while your circulatory system has your heart to pump and clean your blood automatically, your lymph has NO built-in pump whatsoever. ❤️⁣
⁣
Lymph only moves manually through 🏃‍♀️exercise, 💆🏼‍♀️massage, and some 🌿dietary/herbal interventions for support… which is why it’s so easy to get backed up with our modern lifestyle.⁣
⁣
🧠 YOUR BRAIN has it’s own lymphatic system too, called the “glymphatic system,” which was only “discovered” by science in 2015. This means there are lymphatic vessels in your brain that are responsible for brain detoxification while you sleep, including the removal of amyloid plaque which has been implicated in Alzheimer’s Disease. ⁣
⁣
“We had the directors of the National Institute of Health come speak to us, and they were saying that the cure for Alzheimer’s, infections disease, Crohn’s, colitis and other digestive disorders is going to come from studying the lymphatic system.” - @THELYMPHATICMESSAGE 🔥🔥🔥⁣
⁣
Researchers at the University of Virginia are developing a pill to help expand the lymphatic vessels in the brain… but Lisa explained that we can ALL improve our brain’s glymphatic function right this moment with simple at-home self massage techniques. 💊 ⁣
⁣

⁣

In this week’s episode, Dr. Zelina Medina of @acuvida_acupuncture is exploring the link between TRAUMA + chronic illness in order to shine light on the role that emotional and spiritual wellness plays in healing the physical.⁣
⁣
Dr. Zelina has an incredible story of healing, and was led to her career after being diagnosed with the autoimmune disease lupus. ⁣
⁣
Autoimmune disease is exploding right now, and while there are MANY factors that are overstimulating our immune systems, in this clip we’re exploring the emotional layer that relates to boundaries in the lens of Traditional Chinese Medicine.⁣
⁣
According to TCM, the Wei Qi (or Protective Qi) is our immune system. It is our physical AND energetic boundary that protects us not only from pathogens, but from taking on others’ energy and emotions too deeply as well (empaths and those who are extremely sensitive – read up on Wei Qi) 👌🏼⁣
⁣
Wei Qi is circulated and spread by the Lung Qi, and is supported by energy from the Kidney Qi and Spleen Qi (aka the digestive system - think about how eating too much sugar / not getting enough nutrition lowers our immunity).⁣
⁣
In autoimmune disease, the Wei Qi is dysregulated, creating a hypersensitivity, so the first thing that TCM practitioners treat is the Lung meridian that circulates it. It’s also extremely important to nourish the Spleen Qi (digestive fire) and Kidney Qi (adrenals, reproductive system, etc - hello adaptogens!!) 🌿🌿🌿⁣
⁣
My teacher Richard said something during class that mirrors this: in autoimmunity, not only does the immune system become confused about what is “self” and what is “other”, but our boundaries between the self & those around us can become distorted as well (this, of course, can be a result of trauma which brings it full circle).⁣
⁣
Sometimes we let too MUCH in, while other times we shut down after seeing ourselves as too separate from the collective — isolated, unworthy, etc. He says “ultimately, it is a dysregulation in the relationship we have with the world.”⁣
⁣
Dr. Z explains that the way we talk to ourselves (our internal relationship) also has an impact on our immune system. It’s all connected. 🙏🏼💯

node.text:
DID YOU KNOW WALKING DECREASES THE FEAR RESPONSE IN YOUR BRAIN - helping you to have more courage in your daily life?⁣
⁣
A few months ago I was sent a clip from one of my new fave podcasts (besides mine of course😇) called Huberman Lab, where a neuroscience professor breaks down why and how the brain controls our behavior and perception of the world.⁣
⁣
In this clip, Huberman mentioned a 2018 study showing that FORWARD MOVEMENT -- manually moving your body forward through walking, running, swimming, biking and more -- can suppress the brain's fear response and encourage us to be more courageous and confrontational, ready to face life's daily tasks. This forward movement also triggers the release of dopamine, which helps us experience less anxiety.⁣
⁣
He went onto explain that this effect is due to the 'lateralized eye movements' that our eyes engage in (naturally moving from side to side as we take in the environment around us) while we're actively propelling our bodies forward. ⁣
⁣
These lateralized eye movements can help us to change our feelings and perceptions around difficult memories OR current events that are causing us distress... whether that's related to long held trauma, an argument we had with our partner the night before, or even feelings of anxiety & overwhelm when it comes to unread emails in our inbox. This is quite literally the basis of how EMDR therapy was discovered for treating trauma in the first place! 😨💡⁣
⁣
I know that many of you are familiar with EMDR, and it has changed your life just like it has changed mine - but I had no idea walking helps us to mimic these eye moments, too! In a sense, we get a tiny dose of this each time we take a walk, which literally gives a whole new meaning to "clearing your head" (or maybe your eyes 👀) of stressors.⁣
⁣
“Your retinas are not connected to your brain, they ARE your brain! They are pieces of brain that were designed to see objects, but fundamentally they were designed for us to set our internal state of arousal or calm." - Andrew Huberman 🔑⁣
⁣
Yet another reason to get out there and move today - and one more piece of the puzzle as to why walks can truly change your life ❤️

node.text:
HOW SIMPLY WALKING CHANGED MY BODY + LIFE 🤍⁣
⁣
So many of you have asked about my walks over the last few months. ⁣
❌ why I rave about the benefits of such a simple activity⁣
❌ if JUST walking has really made that much of a difference⁣
❌ how I worked up to my current distance & made it a HABIT 🔑 ⁣
⁣
In my coming posts and stories, I hope to answer these Qs and more, starting with a full recap of WHAT MY JOURNEY LOOKED LIKE:⁣
⁣
✨Nov 2020: Even though I knew better, I was the most sedentary I've been in a long time, feeling paralyzed in my head by seasonal affective disorder and a period of intense family & work issues. The last thing I wanted to do was move physically because I felt so much shame about myself, but I knew that was exactly the solution I needed to get back INTO my body and face the stressors in my life head on with a new perspective and healthier brain chemistry.⁣
⁣
✨Dec 2020: I slowly but surely began moving a little more each day until I actually started to like it rather than resist it - didn't LOVE it just yet tho, so I didn't push too hard. Started to feel like maybe I could keep this promise to myself.⁣
⁣
✨Jan 2021: Laughed that if I could get out and walk every day in snow and 20 degree weather, I could do ANYTHING. Bargained with myself that harsh weather would make me tougher and that life's problems wouldn't feel so heavy. It actually worked! Started reading literature on the benefits of walking for insulin resistance, cognition, hormone health, etc to keep motivated. Broke my walks up into 3 x 10-15 mins per day to make it a game.⁣
⁣
✨Feb 2021: BREAKTHROUGH MONTH. I made a promise to only increase distance when it felt like a CHALLENGE not a CHORE, and suddenly everything changed... I wasn't dragging myself out of bed in the morning because I was so used to them that they became second nature and fun. I started feeling more independent, less confined to my house or trapped in my head. I had an outlet, a new relationship with myself. I realized I was 'taking myself out' for the 'fun activity' I always craved as a lonely only child - being my own friend.⁣
⁣
CONT IN COMMENTS 👇🏼👇🏼

node.text:
CHAPTER 3: HOW WE SURPRISED OUR FRIENDS AND FAMILY 💍🦋⁣
⁣
Now, this is the part of the story where the Leo who loves a celebration truly comes out of me 😇 Even though we got engaged 3000 miles away from home in the most perfect & intimate way, we had the video footage saved in time forever, so it was my turn to surprise our family and share the joy 🥺💕⁣
⁣
As soon as I told my girls, we got to planning a “podcast season 2 surprise party” in Nick’s brother and sister in law’s backyard! 😇😇 (Honestly, the best part was keeping the secret from them because they are always so happy for us regardless, and I knew how honored they’d be to find out they hosted THIS!) ❤️⁣
⁣
I had a vision for the party: floor pillows galore with comfy cushions, poufs, side tables. A huge TV screen to play the “trailer” once all the guests arrived so they could feel like they were right there with us. 💍💕 The most decadent dairy and gluten free cake, flowers everywhere, and our favorite bartender to keep the drinks flowing (will share all vendor details next!)⁣
⁣
My girl @hereismaddy came through and saved my life by introducing me to Helen of @bonitodesign, who put my dream surprise reveal party together. I will show you all of her attention to detail soon, but for now picture this...⁣
⁣
It’s 3pm on a Sunday in June. All of our loved ones are around us (wearing neutral shades for “podcast photos”😂), rose margaritas in hand, enjoying a world where we can hold each other again. Mom, dad and Uncle Marty are tucked away at a table catching up with the amazing humans who will unknowingly soon be their official family.⁣
⁣
Nick and I get up on the mic and thank everyone not only for being here today, but for how they showed up for us and my parents in 2020. I never had a chance to fully thank everyone in one place, and this moment meant everything to me. We played the official podcast trailer, with the proposal at the end, and my girls were ready with biodegradable confetti poppers for when he got down on one knee 🥺🎉 ⁣
⁣
The rest is a beautiful blur of love. It was a celebration I’ll never forget, and maybe even the (second) best day of my life thus far 💖

node.text:
CHAPTER 2 of the #engagementchronicles - HOW I SURPRISED MY GIRLFRIENDS 💕🦋⁣
⁣
We left off with Nick shocking me on the last day of our California trip, and it took everything in me not to FaceTime my girls immediately that night. But I knew that this once in a lifetime news — 10 years in the making, marrying someone THEY consider a best friend and brother too — had to be shared in person.⁣
⁣
After spending hours plotting on the plane, I realized that the perfect way to surprise them would be to edit a fake “podcast trailer” and say I needed their honest opinion to give feedback to our editor. This eventually turned into the REAL podcast trailer with the proposal at the end, which we used to surprise our loved ones at a family party - stay tuned for Chapter 3!⁣
⁣
As soon as I got home, I mustered all of my iMovie skills and put together the most janky video (that my girls sat through with love and patience 🤣 bless their hearts). We were scheduled for a girl’s beach day early Sunday morning, so I asked them to come to my house 15 mins before hitting the road for the trailer viewing.⁣
⁣
It just so happened that two of my best friends @elevatedaestheticsspa & @priscillaleeee came over Saturday before the beach as well, and we had the most beautiful evening in the backyard, laying on comfy blankets in the grass and catching up. I swear the sky had never looked so blue; the garden had never felt THIS magical and the energy felt *so right* to seize the moment & tell them in this sacred space.⁣
⁣
At one point, I went in the house to grab us snacks and passed by Nick saying, “I miss my ring! I wish I could tell them NOW!” His face lit up and we both knew it was time, so he came out right behind me with laptop in hand, playing along with my story about needing feedback for this “rough draft.”⁣
⁣
The look on their faces when they realized what they were watching is something I will cherish forever — the deep, genuine love and happiness they felt for us was palpable and just further reminds me why our friendship is one of the most priceless and rare things I’ve ever experienced.⁣
⁣
CONTINUED 🔻🔻🔻

CHAPTER 1.5 - THE BODY & SOUL KNOWS BEFORE THE MIND DOES 👀💛⁣
⁣
One of my personal goals this year, especially with the separation of our official brand instagram @shoporganicolivia, is to get back to my storytelling roots… squeezing the juice 😉🧃 out of each moment through reflection. Life feels like it’s moving faster than ever, and writing helps me slow down so I don’t miss the magic.⁣
⁣
With that being said, I want to start the #engagementcontent saga with a story about the day I got engaged… a tale of how the body holds deep wisdom and awareness before the mind is even conscious of what’s happening. ⁣
⁣
The photos you see above were shot by @yasminediba just hours before Nick got down on one knee, and when I saw the ones of me smiling down at my ring finger, my jaw dropped. I don’t even remember taking these — that joy on my face must have been from my higher self who knew the bliss I was about to experience.⁣
⁣
Here’s where it gets weirder: you see how I’m wearing a dainty ring on my left ring finger?! You guys know me by now: a) I’m superstitious, b) I never get my nails done, and c) I never wear rings. I’m just not a huge fan of my fingers, and I would especially avoid wearing something on that left hand due to old wives tales. 😂⁣
⁣
This day, however, was a full shoot day, and I knew I’d be shooting closeups holding dried herbs on camera. I figured I’d at least try to make my fingers look a *little* cuter, and therefore wore one ring on each hand for symmetry.⁣
⁣
As soon as I came down the stairs that morning and my team saw my finger, they apparently looked around in panic, pulling each other aside saying, “What is she doing?! She never wears rings in the first place; who’s going to get her to take it off? How do we tell her to remove it without raising suspicion?” After hours of going back and forth, Nick and the girls decided they’d just have to let it be, because preserving the surprise meant 10x more.⁣
⁣
CONTINUED IN COMMENTS 🔻

BIG ANNOUNCEMENT #1 & GIVEAWAY: THE NEXT CHAPTER OF ORGANIC OLIVIA 🦋⁣
⁣
Not only are we thrilled to share our new OFFICIAL BRAND INSTAGRAM: @shoporganicolivia 👑 ⁣
⁣
...we are also hosting a HUGE giveaway on the @shoporganicolivia feed for 5 lucky winners to celebrate!!🎈🎉 ⁣
⁣
🌟 WHY A NEW IG HUB FOR OO CONTENT? ⁣
⁣
As many of you know, a theme that has been coming up me this year is beautiful BOUNDARIES, whether in personal life or business. My Instagram, this community, and the company Nick and I have both worked so hard to build in different ways has evolved so many times over the last 8+ years, and I’ve realized two things: ⁣
⁣
a) that we’re really doing this. Organic Olivia is a grown-up, worldwide brand and our formulas, podcasts and education have the ability to change lives and make a true difference. We are in it for the long haul and this is only the beginning of our professional journey. ⁣
⁣
b) that I also love sharing the moments in between, my personal health journey and learnings (which is how this all started), my philosophies, my daily walks and musings as an herbalist and human who wants to keep teaching separate from just my brand alone. ⁣
⁣
💕FOR THAT REASON, @shoporganicolivia will be our official brand Instagram serving up valuable educational posts and articles, digital “meet the herb” monographs, infographics, Nick’s recipes with carousel cards of ingredients & directions for easy saving, product info, weekly podcast features with Q&A/IGTV content with our guests, and SO MUCH MORE. I finally realized that I can’t do it all myself and put a team in place to make this professional move happen 👏🏼 ⁣
⁣
💕My personal Instagram where you are now @organic_olivia will stay exactly the same as what it’s evolved to; I’ll always be here sharing my daily walks and stories, family life, what I’m reading and eating, personal health journey tips etc. I’ll be able to share with even less pressure because the heart and soul of my baby, my business, is so deeply held and supported. ⁣
⁣
Follow @shoporganicolivia to find all giveaway details and rules in today’s feed post! Plus, check my stories today for a full breakdown of what you’ll win 🦋🦋🦋

GARDEN UPDATE + PRUNING TOMATOES FOR JUICIER FRUIT 🍅 so excited to share this growth, and I need help from this amazing community with my brussels and beets (see last slide!) 🌱⁣
⁣
SLIDE 1: Living my best Italian nonna life trimming tomato branches to prevent crowding, especially since they’re planted so close. We’ve already been pinching the “suckers” that sprout up in the “elbows” between the main stem and branches, but we’re also clipping the first 6-12 inches of baby branches to conserve nutrients for juicier fruit. I’ll share in stories a video from @epicgardening that taught me how to pinch suckers.⁣
⁣
SLIDES 2 + 3: This is the tomato progress from May 15 to June 10 😳 Shoutout to Nick’s brother @_scottyv for watering them while we were gone, apparently he has the same green thumb as Nick!⁣
⁣

⁣
SLIDE 7: This is how I trim the lettuce when we’re ready to eat and it’s getting too crowded; only take the outer leaves and pinch/twist them at the bottom so that the middle leaves can keep growing up straight and eventually billow out to be picked.⁣
⁣
SLIDES 8 + 9: If you love cilantro like we do, you’ll appreciate this 😂🌿 We put it in a pot this year instead of a bed so we can take it inside before it BOLTS in the heat! Lesson learned.⁣
⁣
